            <div class="info-container">
                <h2>Nutritional Needs for Cats</h2>
                <p>Cats require a diet rich in certain nutrients to stay healthy:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Protein:</strong> Essential for muscle development and overall health. Include high-quality meat sources like chicken, turkey, and fish.</li>
                    <li><strong>Fat:</strong> Provides energy and supports a healthy coat. Look for sources like fish oil or chicken fat.</li>
                    <li><strong>Vitamins and Minerals:</strong> Ensure they receive essential vitamins like A, D, and E through balanced cat food or supplements.</li>
                    <li><strong>Water:</strong> Always provide fresh water to prevent dehydration and support kidney function.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Avoid feeding them dog food or human food that can be toxic to them, such as onions and garlic.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Environmental Needs -->
        <section class="info-section">
            <div class="info-container">
                <h2>Ideal Environment for Cats</h2>
                <p>Creating a comfortable and safe environment is crucial for cats:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Sleeping Area:</strong> Provide a soft, cozy bed in a quiet area of your home where they feel secure.</li>
                    <li><strong>Outdoor Access:</strong> If possible, provide a safe outdoor enclosure or supervised time outside to stimulate their natural instincts.</li>
                    <li><strong>Temperature:</strong> Maintain a comfortable indoor temperature, avoiding extremes of heat or cold.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Ensure their environment is free from hazards and provide enrichment like toys and scratching posts.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Common Diseases and Prevention -->
        <section class="info-section">
            <div class="info-container">
                <h2>Common Health Issues and Prevention</h2>
                <p>Understanding common health issues helps in prevention and management:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Feline Lower Urinary Tract Disease (FLUTD):</strong> Monitor for signs of urinary issues and ensure a balanced diet to prevent crystals.</li>
                    <li><strong>Fleas and Ticks:</strong> Use preventive treatments and regularly check for parasites.</li>
                    <li><strong>Dental Issues:</strong> Regular brushing and dental check-ups can prevent tartar buildup and gum disease.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Regular vet visits and vaccinations are essential for overall health and disease prevention.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Health Maintenance and Best Practices -->
        <section class="info-section">
